    <h1>THE PHILIP&#xAD;PINES: BLK COS&#xAD;MET&#xAD;ICS</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201106/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-06"><time>2020-11-06</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>An­other Filipino favourite, BLK Cos­met­ics, too, has a celebrity at its helm: Filipino-Aus­tralian ac­tress Anne Curtis-Smith (left), who also serves as the face of the brand.</p>
    <p>The make-up line, launched in 2017, has ev­ery­thing you need for a full face – from foun­da­tion and brow pen­cils to blushes, tinted sun­screens, lip­sticks and more. Most of the prod­ucts are priced un­der</p>
    <p>500 pe­sos (S$14).</p>
    <p>BLK Cos­met­ics does not ship in­ter­na­tion­ally, but is stocked on e-re­tailer Zalora Philip­pines and at Wat­sons stores in the Philip­pines.</p>

